# Park Chorus

## Step

Resolved when: (1) session starts no longer inject the "Rhizomatic
briefing" (find the hook/injection point — evidence: the 2026-07-17
grilling session received one with zero preferences, zero tasks,
June-stale topics); (2) the 13-mutation outbox is snapshotted to a file
(NAS or `.brain/data/`) before being discarded — nothing becomes a live
claim; (3) the Chorus/rhizome service is stopped and disabled
(launchd/daemon receipt showing it down), with the restart path
documented in this file; (4) nothing is deleted — parked, not razed.
Evidence base:
[periphery survey](../memory-system-review/periphery-survey.svx)
"Rhizomatic / Chorus claims" + flag #2, and the
[decision](../memory-system-repair/decide-chorus-fate.svx).

## Result

Worker-side parking completed on Flagg on 2026-07-17. The service stop is
still pending because the task reserves `launchctl bootout` for steering.
Do not mark this step closed until steering runs the stop commands and records
