### Briefing injection parked

Executed machine-local edits:

1. Removed the Rhizomatic `SessionStart` and `Stop` groups from
   `~/.claude/settings.json`. Preserved the JoelClaw Run-capture `Stop` hook
   and `dcg` `PreToolUse` hook.
2. Removed the Rhizomatic `SessionStart` and `Stop` groups from
   `~/.codex/hooks.json`. Preserved the JoelClaw Run-capture `Stop` hook and
   `dcg` `PreToolUse` hook.
3. Removed `../../Code/joelhooks/pi-rhizomatic` from the Pi package list in
   `~/.pi/agent/settings.json`.

All three files are ordinary user-owned files, not symlinks. A targeted search
found no corresponding Rhizomatic hook/package source in `dark-wizard`; these
are Flagg machine-local edits and need no dark-wizard commit. The hook scripts,
Rhizomatic config, package checkout, outbox, and service files remain intact.
Fresh Claude, Codex, and Pi processes will not inject the briefing. Pi processes
that were already running when settings changed keep the extension loaded until
they exit.

This idempotent command reproduces the parking edits without disturbing other
hooks:

```bash
python3 <<'PY'
import json
from pathlib import Path

for path in (Path.home() / ".claude/settings.json", Path.home() / ".codex/hooks.json"):
    data = json.loads(path.read_text())
    hooks = data.get("hooks", {})
    for event in ("SessionStart", "Stop"):
        groups = hooks.get(event, [])
        kept = [
            group
            for group in groups
            if not any(
                "rhizomatic" in str(hook.get("command", "")).lower()
                for hook in group.get("hooks", [])
                if isinstance(hook, dict)
            )
        ]
        if kept:
            hooks[event] = kept
        else:
            hooks.pop(event, None)
    path.write_text(json.dumps(data, indent=2) + "\n")

path = Path.home() / ".pi/agent/settings.json"
data = json.loads(path.read_text())
data["packages"] = [
    package
    for package in data.get("packages", [])
    if package != "../../Code/joelhooks/pi-rhizomatic"
]
path.write_text(json.dumps(data, indent=2) + "\n")
PY
```

### Steering-only service stop

Run exactly this from an administrator account. The first command prevents a
future load; the second stops and unloads the current KeepAlive daemon.

```bash
sudo launchctl disable system/com.joelclaw.chorus-rhizomatic
sudo launchctl bootout system /Library/LaunchDaemons/com.joelclaw.chorus-rhizomatic.plist

# Required down-state receipts:
! launchctl print system/com.joelclaw.chorus-rhizomatic
launchctl print-disabled system | grep 'com.joelclaw.chorus-rhizomatic'
! nc -z 127.0.0.1 4821
```

Expected receipts: `launchctl print` cannot find the service, the disabled map
shows `=> disabled`, and the port probe fails. Do not boot out or modify the
already-disabled legacy label as part of this step.

### Un-park path

The service restart path is:

```bash
sudo launchctl enable system/com.joelclaw.chorus-rhizomatic
sudo launchctl bootstrap system /Library/LaunchDaemons/com.joelclaw.chorus-rhizomatic.plist
sudo launchctl kickstart -k system/com.joelclaw.chorus-rhizomatic
launchctl print system/com.joelclaw.chorus-rhizomatic
nc -zv 127.0.0.1 4821
```

Only restore automatic runtime injection after explicitly deciding to revive
Chorus. The parked wrapper scripts remain under `~/.config/rhizomatic/hooks/`.
This exact command restores their hook references and the Pi package:

```bash
python3 <<'PY'
import json
from pathlib import Path

def add_group(groups, group):
    command = group["hooks"][0]["command"]
    if not any(
        hook.get("command") == command
        for existing in groups
        for hook in existing.get("hooks", [])
        if isinstance(hook, dict)
    ):
        groups.append(group)

claude = Path.home() / ".claude/settings.json"
data = json.loads(claude.read_text())
hooks = data.setdefault("hooks", {})
add_group(hooks.setdefault("Stop", []), {
    "matcher": "",
    "hooks": [{
        "type": "command",
        "command": "bash '/Users/joel/.config/rhizomatic/hooks/claude-stop.sh'",
        "timeout": 10000,
    }],
})
add_group(hooks.setdefault("SessionStart", []), {
    "matcher": "*",
    "hooks": [{
        "type": "command",
        "command": "bash '/Users/joel/.config/rhizomatic/hooks/claude-session-start.sh'",
        "timeout": 10000,
    }],
})
claude.write_text(json.dumps(data, indent=2) + "\n")

codex = Path.home() / ".codex/hooks.json"
data = json.loads(codex.read_text())
hooks = data.setdefault("hooks", {})
add_group(hooks.setdefault("Stop", []), {
    "hooks": [{
        "type": "command",
        "command": "bash '/Users/joel/.config/rhizomatic/hooks/codex-stop.sh'",
        "timeout": 10000,
    }],
})
add_group(hooks.setdefault("SessionStart", []), {
    "hooks": [{
        "type": "command",
        "command": "bash '/Users/joel/.config/rhizomatic/hooks/codex-session-start.sh'",
        "timeout": 10000,
    }],
})
codex.write_text(json.dumps(data, indent=2) + "\n")

pi = Path.home() / ".pi/agent/settings.json"
data = json.loads(pi.read_text())
package = "../../Code/joelhooks/pi-rhizomatic"
packages = data.setdefault("packages", [])
if package not in packages:
    marker = "git:github.com/joelhooks/pi-ast-grep@main"
    packages.insert(packages.index(marker) if marker in packages else len(packages), package)
pi.write_text(json.dumps(data, indent=2) + "\n")
PY
```

Start fresh Claude, Codex, and Pi processes after restoring the configuration.
Never drain the parked snapshot/outbox as part of un-parking without a new,
explicit promotion decision.

